First published by GroundUp First published by GroundUp First published by GroundUp About 30 students and workers were protesting outside the Faculty of Education building on Monday when police and private security dispersed them using pepper spray and stun grenades. About 30 students and workers were protesting outside the Faculty of Education building on Monday when police and private security dispersed them using pepper spray and stun grenades. About 30 students and workers were protesting outside the Faculty of Education building on Monday when police and private security dispersed them using pepper spray and stun grenades. A protester argues with police after pepper spray had been used on protesters. A protester argues with police after pepper spray had been used on protesters. A protester argues with police after pepper spray had been used on protesters. At the time that GroundUp was at the protest, it appeared mostly peaceful. But one protester tried to break through a police and private security line protecting the building. The police then used stun grenades and pepper spray to disperse the protesters. The protester who tried to break the line was detained. One student was dragged by his legs, and others were involved in scuffles with private security. Some protesters threw rocks at police during the altercations. Students reported being fired at with rubber bullets. At the time that GroundUp was at the protest, it appeared mostly peaceful. But one protester tried to break through a police and private security line protecting the building. The police then used stun grenades and pepper spray to disperse the protesters. The protester who tried to break the line was detained. One student was dragged by his legs, and others were involved in scuffles with private security. Some protesters threw rocks at police during the altercations. Students reported being fired at with rubber bullets. At the time that GroundUp was at the protest, it appeared mostly peaceful. 